mages/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Crispy-Halloumi-Tomatoes-and-White2-hmvk-vjzg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Crispy-Halloumi-Tomatoes-and-White2-hmvk-vjzg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLinda Xiao for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Judy Kim.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eA quick read-through of the comments, or \u003ca href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/NYTCooking/\" title=\"\"\u003eReddit\u003c/a\u003e, will tell you that this is one of those rare recipes that racks up win after win: It’s supremely easy, packed with plant-based protein and takes 30 minutes (or even less). Our suggestion is to listen to the commenters who recommend doubling up on everything — this dish is sure to go fast.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1026520-crispy-halloumi-with-tomatoes-and-white-beans\" title=\"\"\u003eCrispy Halloumi With Tomatoes and White Beans\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-3f50ba28\"\u003e4. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1025016-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw\" title=\"\"\u003eBreaded Halloumi With Cabbage Slaw\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"An overhead image of a breaded block of halloumi and a small cabbage slaw on a plate next to spent lemon wedges.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw-pwfl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLinda Xiao for The New York Times\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you’re craving chicken or pork katsu, consider this vegetarian recipe from Hetty Lui McKinnon, which swaps in halloumi for the meat. Cornstarch in the flour and a dash of oil in the egg help the breadcrumbs adhere, giving the final product a wonderful crunch.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1025016-breaded-halloumi-with-cabbage-slaw\" title=\"\"\u003eBreaded Halloumi With Cabbage Slaw\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-1e40cdbc\"\u003e5. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1022548-pesto-pasta-with-white-beans-and-halloum\" title=\"\"\u003ePesto Pasta With White Beans and Halloumi\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"An overhead image of pasta in a wide-rimmed bowl tossed with creamy white beans and grated cheese.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-One-Pan-Pesto-Pasta-mgwb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eChristopher Simpson for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eIn this weeknight recipe, Yotam Ottolenghi ingeniously suggests grating the halloumi over your pasta, like traditional Parmesan but tangier. And, after you’ve liberally dolloped the simple arugula pesto the pasta, you’ll want to spoon it onto everything.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1022548-pesto-pasta-with-white-beans-and-halloum\" title=\"\"\u003ePesto Pasta With White Beans and Halloumi\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-56c39828\"\u003e6. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1025202-taverna-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eTaverna Salad\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Cubed halloumi, chickpeas and tomatoes are tossed together and photographed on a large platter.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-Taverna-Salad-wclg-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDavid Malosh for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis hearty salad, from Lidey Heuck’s “Cooking in Real Life,” has quickly become a reader favorite, with more than 6,300 five-star ratings. It takes inspiration from classic \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1021079-greek-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eGreek salad\u003c/a\u003e (also known as horiatiki) and Lebanese \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/10709-fattoush-lebanese-tomato-and-pita-salad\" title=\"\"\u003efattoush\u003c/a\u003e. The fried pita and halloumi add the perfect warm crunch to complement the fresh ingredients, and the result is a salad hearty enough to eat for a meal (or several).\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1025202-taverna-salad\" title=\"\"\u003eTaverna Salad\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-2c7dd2e7\"\u003e7. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1026376-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers\" title=\"\"\u003eHalloumi-Stuffed Sweet Peppers\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"An overhead image of small cheese-filled peppers on crostini.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers-gjzl-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eKelly Marshall for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Samantha Seneviratne.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis super-easy appetizer from Melissa Clark is just what it sounds like: roasted, garlicky mini peppers baked with halloumi inside, and served on crostini. Consider it the perfect finger food for any gathering if you’re short on time.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1026376-halloumi-stuffed-sweet-peppers\" title=\"\"\u003eHalloumi-Stuffed Sweet Peppers\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-5f41b7af\"\u003e8. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1022435-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi\" title=\"\"\u003eCorn Salad With Mango and Halloumi\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"An overhead image of corn and mango tossed with cucumbers and halloumi in a black bowl.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi-zbvp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eDavid Malosh for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Simon Andrews.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eGood mangoes are one of life’s greatest joys. So are recipes that make use of their juicy sweetness. Two other summer gems, corn and cucumbers, adorn this recipe from Hetty Lui McKinnon. And, of course, lightly pan-fried halloumi adds balance and a savory bite.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1022435-corn-salad-with-mango-and-halloumi\" title=\"\"\u003eCorn Salad With Mango and Halloumi\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-644ddfca\"\u003e9. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1018749-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava\" title=\"\"\u003eWalnut, Cinnamon and Halloumi Baklava\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A side image of several squares of baklava, the nutty insides exposed.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava-pjqb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAndrew Scrivani for The New York Times\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eDon’t fear: You won’t need to make your own phyllo pastry for Yotam Ottolenghi’s version of this classic dessert. Halloumi is the perfect savory backdrop for the rose water syrup and sweet, spiced walnut filling in this baklava, staying soft if you serve the baklava warm.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1018749-walnut-cinnamon-and-halloumi-baklava\" title=\"\"\u003eWalnut, Cinnamon and Halloumi Baklava\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-69e586fe\"\u003e10. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1025089-halloumi-chicken-parmesan-with-zaatar\" title=\"\"\u003eHalloumi Chicken Parmesan With Za’atar\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"An overhead image of chicken topped with melted halloumi and za’atar next to a green salad.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/02/17/magazine/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-chicken-parm-copy/17mag-Eat-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/02/17/magazine/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-chicken-parm-copy/17mag-Eat-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/02/17/magazine/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-chicken-parm-copy/17mag-Eat-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/02/17/magazine/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-chicken-parm-copy/17mag-Eat-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/02/17/magazine/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-chicken-parm-copy/17mag-Eat-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2024/02/17/magazine/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-halloumi-chicken-parm-copy/17mag-Eat-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eLinda Xiao for The New York Times. Food stylist: Maggie Ruggiero. Prop stylist: Andie McMahon.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eHalloumi steps in for mozzarella in this classic Italian American dish with a distinctly Yotam Ottolenghi twist. Cumin and allspice jazz up a can of diced tomatoes, and za’atar is used in both the panko crumb coating and the earthy oil drizzled on top, making this familiar comfort feel new.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1025089-halloumi-chicken-parmesan-with-zaatar\" title=\"\"\u003eHalloumi Chicken Parmesan With Za’atar\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-4a079ff\"\u003e11. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1020773-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi\" title=\"\"\u003eSkillet Chicken With Couscous, Lemon and Halloumi\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A skillet filled with burnished chicken parts is topped with shallot rings, cheese and herbs.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi-pvjb-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eJohnny Miller for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Rebecca Jurkevich.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eYewande Komolafe’s skillet chicken is simple enough to make on a weekday, but the additions of toasted walnuts, shallots, oregano and torn, marinated halloumi make this dish dinner-party elegant.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1020773-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi\" title=\"\"\u003eS\u003c/a\u003e\u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1020773-skillet-chicken-with-couscous-lemon-and-halloumi\" title=\"\"\u003ekillet Chicken With Couscous, Lemon and Halloumi\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"link-16706d03\"\u003e12. \u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1017591-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables\" title=\"\"\u003eGrilled Halloumi and Vegetables\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Slabs of halloumi with grill marks lay on a bed of grilled mixed vegetables.\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"100vw\" srcset=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 320w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 480w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 768w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1024w, https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp 1280w\" src=\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2025/07/07/multimedia/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp/07FD-HALLOUMI-ROUNDUP-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables-fwtp-superJumbo.jpg?quality=75\u0026amp;auto=webp\"/\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eRachel Vanni for The New York Times. Food Stylist: Spencer Richards.\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis Martha Rose Shulman recipe is extremely simple, and that’s just where its charms begin: The halloumi is brushed with olive oil, and grilled alongside vegetables before receiving a shower of herbs and sumac, if you’re feeling fancy. The ideal weekend-by-the-grill main.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eRecipe: \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1017591-grilled-halloumi-and-vegetables\" title=\"\"\u003eGrilled Halloumi and Vegetables\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eFollow \u003c/em\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nytcooking/\" title=\"\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eNew York Times Cooking on Instagram\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003cem\u003e, \u003c/em